            <!-- Text -->
            <p class="text-justify">
              Jazztel has been created in 1998 and has a huge appetite to grab a share of the Telco market in Spain controlled by its incumbent Telefonica. With 3kms of infratructure, they funded their huge capex need by opening their capital. The first step of it was 60m$ equity raised with Apax in Q1-1999. Alongside with this equity
              , they get used to tap the High yield debt market raising 200m$ in Q2-1999, 400m$ prior to their IPO in December 1999 and 225m$ in Q2-2000 at market peak.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-0 text-justify">
              Their IPO is an odyssey very well described in a infamous Harvard Business School case. It happened on December 8th 1999, Jazztel raised 196m€ and was valued at that time just a little bit less of 1bn€, almost a Unicorn.
              They did not even been introduced in Madrid but in the Nasdaq! Remember it was in 1999, totally different times....
            </p>
